# Selection 

## 1. Activation Layers

### Selection

At the core our face key-points model has classical two parts CNN architecture that suits well in many visual recognition projects. Part 1 constitutional with wedge type architecture of guessed layer sizes.  Second part is fully connected MLP with output layer to fit regression to 30 key-point positions. As first step we need to check if guessed sizes of layers are adequate to learn on our data set.

The model demonstrates accuracy 0.7 and MSE 0.005 with hyper-parameters set to fit training on CPU. This level of performance proves size of base NN is appropriate for initial selection. 

A change in random seed initialization demonstrates significant effect on performance. For future experiments in model selection we fixed random seed to compare models with similar initialization and minimize effect of randomness in learning performance. It should server our goal in educational purpose. The accurate approach would require to add seed as parameter in model selection process.

In the search we used different activation method inside first convolution layer and hidden layer of MLP. The Idea behind different activations in constitutional layer to make first CNN layer output binary-kind image and automatically learn "features" similar to edge detection.  Changes in hidden layer just to see if that affects learning capability of MLP. The results are shown in the next section.

-  reLu + sigmoid

  The standard choice seen in many implementation. This model serves as base line. accuracy 0.7 and MSE 0.005

- reLu + linear

  With accuracy 0.75 and MSE 0.002 is significantly better than base line.

- linear + linear

  accuracy 0.75 and MSE 0.002 it is very similar to reLu + linear combination. However the learning process is definitely more smooth.simmiar

- sigmoid  + linear

  The model exhibits very early saturation in accuracy around 0.7 compare to other models fluctuating above 0.7. Possible the resolution of first layer is the limit?

- sigmoid x10 + linear

  The Idea to add 10 times filters into first layer to overcome 0.7 limit. The result is negative. Saturation on 0.7 accuracy persists. Size of first layer is not the limit. Rejecting sigmoid  + linear combination.

Selection choice: **linear + linear**.
